c:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"10Gbps LiFi arrives—if your desk lamp stays on"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Plug-and-play vs. line-of-sight’s harsh tradeoff"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Taara’s rival bets on speed over real-world flexibility"}]]}]]}]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Forget wrestling with Ethernet cables or praying for stable Wi-Fi in a crowded office. ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://purelifi.com","children":"pureLiFi"}]," just dropped a 10Gbps wireless solution that plugs in like a desk lamp—literally. Their new LiFi system leverages LED light waves to transmit data at fiber-like speeds, promising a near-instant, interference-free network for indoor spaces. The pitch is seductive: no spectrum licensing, no radio waves, and a setup so simple it borders on magical."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["But here’s the catch: LiFi only works when your device ",["$","em",null,{"children":"sees"}]," the light. Move your laptop into a shadow, tilt it away from the ceiling fixture, or—god forbid—someone leans against the lamp, and your 10Gbps pipeline collapses into a buffering spiral. This isn’t a bug; it’s the physics. While ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.techradar.com/news/purelifi-10gbps-lifi","children":"TechRadar’s coverage"}]," highlights the plug-and-play convenience, the fine print reveals a technology that demands ",["$","em",null,{"children":"perfect"}]," line-of-sight, a luxury most real-world offices can’t afford."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The competitive framing is just as telling. pureLiFi positions itself as a rival to ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://x.company/projects/taara/","children":"Taara"}],", Alphabet’s laser-based internet project, which also requires clear paths but targets outdoor, long-range connections. pureLiFi’s bet is that indoor users will trade flexibility for raw speed—a gamble that ignores how often people ",["$","em",null,{"children":"move"}]," in shared spaces."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/lifis-10gbps-promise-collides-with-realitys-walls/subtitle.jpg","alt":"The gap between lab specs and office chaos","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"The gap between lab specs and office chaos"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Let’s talk practical impact. For static workstations—think trading floors, control rooms, or server monitoring—LiFi’s speed could be a game-changer, assuming the lights stay on (and unobstructed). But for the average office? The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://standards.ieee.org/standard/802_11bb-2023.html","children":"IEEE’s standards work"}]," on LiFi notes that even ambient light interference can degrade performance. That’s a non-starter for open-plan layouts or teams that, you know, ",["$","em",null,{"children":"collaborate"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Cost is the other unanswered question. pureLiFi’s setup ",["$","em",null,{"children":"appears"}]," cheaper than Taara’s infrastructure-heavy approach, but the total price includes more than hardware. Retrofitting offices with LiFi-compatible lighting, training staff to avoid “shadowing” devices, and maintaining alignment in dynamic spaces could erase any savings. Early adopters might include ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/lifi-could-enhance-hospital-wi-fi-security-and-speed","children":"hospitals"}]," or secure facilities where RF silence is critical, but mainstream offices? The math gets fuzzy fast."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The real signal here isn’t the speed—it’s the tradeoff. pureLiFi is betting that users will tolerate LiFi’s quirks for a spec-sheet win. But in an era where hybrid work demands ","$L15",", not just bandwidth, that’s a risky assumption. The tech press is buzzing, but the ","$L16"," is already flagging the obvious: if your wireless network breaks when someone stands up, it’s not really wireless."]}],"\n","$L17"]}]
