17:["$","p",null,{"children":"For IT decision-makers, the calculus is simple: LiFi’s 10Gbps is enticing, but the hidden costs—redeploying furniture, enforcing “no-shadow” policies, or installing redundant Wi-Fi backups—could outweigh the benefits. The sweet spot might be niche applications where RF interference is a dealbreaker, like manufacturing floors or surgical theaters. Everywhere else, it’s a hard sell."}]
